### 🌐 **Crisis‑Support Playbook – Sample CSS Style Guide**

```css
:root {
  /* Brand + base colors */
  --color-calm: #1E6F8B;      /* blue‑green background */
  --color-action: #F7A200;    /* amber highlight */
  --color-neutral: #ECECEC;   /* panel bg */
  --color-text-dark: #222222;
  --color-text-light: #FFFFFF;

  /* Typography */
  --font-header: 'Open Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
  --font-body: 'Open Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
  --font-size-header: 1.25rem;
  --font-size-body: 1rem;

  /* Spacing */
  --space-sm: 0.5rem;
  --space-md: 1rem;
  --space-lg: 1.5rem;
}

/* Module bands */
.band-engage   {background-color: var(--color-calm); color: var(--color-text-light);}
.band-ground   {background-color: #62B4C9;}
.band-connect  {background-color: var(--color-action); color: var(--color-text-light);}
.band-selfcare {background-color: #D6D8E0;}

/* Icons sizing */
.icon {width: 1.2em; height: 1.2em; vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 0.25em;}

/* Hotline footer */
.footer-hotline {
  background-color: var(--color-action);
  color: var(--color-text-light);
  font-weight: bold;
  text-align: center;
  padding: var(--space-md);
}
```

This starter CSS establishes the palette, fonts, and spacing from your design brief. A developer can extend it with responsive rules (e.g., accordion behaviors, larger buttons) and accessibility states.

